catch(err)
{}}</script> <form class=comment-form id=commentform method=post ><div id=wpcr_div_2> <input type=hidden id=frating name=frating> <input type=hidden id=rating name=rating> <input type=hidden id=author name=author> <input type=hidden id=comment name=comment> <input type=hidden id=email name=email> <input type=hidden id=comment_post_ID name=comment_post_ID value=2835> <input type=hidden id=comment_parent name=comment_parent value=0><table id=wpcr_table_2><tbody><tr><td colspan=2><div id=wpcr_postcomment><h3 id="reply-title" class="comment-reply-title" style="font-size:19px;">Leave a Reply <span style=font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;> ( * fields are required)</span></h3></div></td></tr><tr><td><label for=NXz-fname class=comment-field>Name: *</label></td><td><input class=text-input type=text id=NXz-fname name=NXz-fname value></td></tr><tr><td><label for=zOKj-femail class=comment-field>Email: *</label></td><td><input class=text-input type=text id=zOKj-femail name=zOKj-femail value></td></tr><tr><td><label class=comment-field>Rating:</label></td><td><span class=rating> <input type=radio class=rating-input value=5 id=rating-input-1-5 aria-label=rating-input-1-5 name=rating_val> <label for=rating-input-1-5 class=rating-star></label> <input type=radio class=rating-input value=4 id=rating-input-1-4 aria-label=rating-input-1-4 name=rating_val> <label for=rating-input-1-4 class=rating-star></label> <input type=radio class=rating-input value=3 id=rating-input-1-3 aria-label=rating-input-1-3 name=rating_val> <label for=rating-input-1-3 class=rating-star></label> <input type=radio class=rating-input value=2 id=rating-input-1-2 aria-label=rating-input-1-2 name=rating_val> <label for=rating-input-1-2 class=rating-star></label> <input type=radio class=rating-input value=1 id=rating-input-1-1 aria-label=rating-input-1-1 name=rating_val> <label for=rating-input-1-1 class=rating-star></label> </span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2><label for=P-ftext class=comment-field>Comment: *</label></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2><textarea id=P-ftext name=P-ftext rows=5 cols=100></textarea></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 id=wpcr_check_confirm><div class=wpcr_clear></div> <input type=checkbox name=jJ-fconfirm1 id=fconfirm1 value=1><div class=wpcr_fl><input type=checkbox name=AHe-fconfirm2 id=fconfirm2 value=1></div><div class=wpcr_fl style="margin:-2px 0px 0px 5px"><label for=fconfirm2>Check this box to confirm you are not a robot.</label></div><div class=wpcr_clear></div> <input type=checkbox name=otM-fconfirm3 id=fconfirm3 value=1></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2><input id=wpcr_submit_btn name=submitwpcr_2835 type=submit value="Submit Comment"></td></tr></tbody></table></div></form><hr></div><div class=wpcr_clear></div></div><div class=stars-avg-rating><span class=rating-text><h3><a href=#comments>21 Comments</a></h3></span></div><h2 class="screen-reader-text">Reader Interactions</h2><div class=entry-comments id=comments><h3>Comments</h3><ol class=comment-list> <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-9131><article id=article-comment-9131><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Chetan</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>March 1, 2025 at 11:13 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Simple, easy to make and extremely useful for singles/bachelors. Keep it up.</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-8834><article id=article-comment-8834><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Salony</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>July 23, 2023 at 1:40 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>The method is very well explained. We can add urad dal and rava in the proportion of 1:2 also. Thanks</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:80% class="rating-stars average rt_cls4"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-8768><article id=article-comment-8768><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Ranu</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>April 12, 2023 at 12:21 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hello, easy recipe. Can I make dosa with this better?</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:80% class="rating-stars average rt_cls4"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-7960><article id=article-comment-7960><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Rosy</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>April 3, 2021 at 12:00 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>My ravva is very old. Is this the reason idlis are not white and also they are hard?</p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment even depth-2" id=comment-11221><article id=article-comment-11221><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Yes Rosy, the reasons behind the hard idlis are -1. Batter is not fermented enough, 2. Batter is too thick, 3.the color of the idli depends on the color of the rava.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id=comment-7783><article id=article-comment-7783><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Anuradha Madhavan</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>December 3, 2020 at 8:24 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Excellent.. Great job.. Very easy to follow.. Thanks so much</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-7706><article id=article-comment-7706><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Niaina</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>October 16, 2020 at 7:44 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Can we substitute urad dal with any other dal?</p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-11176><article id=article-comment-11176><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hi Naina, you cannot substitute urad dal with any other dal in this recipe.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-7326><article id=article-comment-7326><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>anandhi</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>May 19, 2020 at 1:27 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hi</p><p>happy morning, the step 8, would like to know when you grind idli rava for smooth texture should we add water and grind it if so how many tablespoons of water I want precise measurement please?</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-11061><article id=article-comment-11061><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hello Anandhi, add the water as needed to make the smooth batter. I will try to give you the exact measurement later.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-6822><article id=article-comment-6822><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Sachi</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>April 9, 2019 at 9:45 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hi, which poha do you use, thin or thick?</p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-10933><article id=article-comment-10933><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hi Sachi, you can use any type of poha (thick or thin).</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-6748><article id=article-comment-6748><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Sadhna</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>January 25, 2019 at 12:15 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>One more question can I add salt after the fermentation of batter</p><p>Thanks</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-10918><article id=article-comment-10918><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Yes, you can add salt after the fermentation.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-6018><article id=article-comment-6018><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Shri</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>February 4, 2018 at 7:00 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Best idli receipe..thanks for sharing</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id=comment-5804><article id=article-comment-5804><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>A.Deivanayaki</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>November 29, 2017 at 2:59 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Very nice recipes&#8230;..<br> All recipes  easily understandable&#8230;..Your step by step photos very useful for leaners.</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-5746><article id=article-comment-5746><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Dishha</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>November 10, 2017 at 5:57 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Can we make dosa from this batter?</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-10710><article id=article-comment-10710><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>I am not sure about it but you can try.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-5677><article id=article-comment-5677><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Samara sultana</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>October 18, 2017 at 4:52 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hi, thank you for the recipe.<br> I would like to know if soda isn&#8217;t required here, if yes then when do we have to add and if not?</p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-10694><article id=article-comment-10694><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hello Samara, soda is not required to make the idlis if the batter is fermented properly. If the batter is not fermented well, you can add a pinch of soda to the batter to make soft idlis.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-5587><article id=article-comment-5587><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Richa</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>September 27, 2017 at 3:57 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Very well explained recipe. GREAT JOB. This is the second time I am going to make it. Specifically searched for this page because I did not want to miss anything.</p></div></article> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id=comment-5111><article id=article-comment-5111><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Samira</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>May 25, 2017 at 9:32 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>I forgot to grind the idly rawa and added to the urad dal paste and the fermentation already started. I don&#8217;t like idlies grainy. Please suggest if I may grind the fermented batter before making idlis to make it less grainy.</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:80% class="rating-stars average rt_cls4"></span></div></p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment even depth-2" id=comment-10581><article id=article-comment-10581><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hello Samira, don&#8217;t grind the already fermented batter because if you grind it again, the texture of the batter will change (fermentation bubbles will disappear) and idli will not turn soft.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-5063><article id=article-comment-5063><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Priyanka</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>May 9, 2017 at 11:24 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Can I skip the fenugreek seeds? Or is there a substitute for them?</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment even depth-2" id=comment-10567><article id=article-comment-10567><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Hello Priyanka, adding fenugreek seeds helps in the fermentation process. If you are living in cold climate, don&#8217;t skip adding fenugreek seeds for better fermentation else you can skip it.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id=comment-4763><article id=article-comment-4763><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Bhavana</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>February 21, 2017 at 3:15 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Very well explained..I mainly wanted to  know whether grinding the rava is essential or not and found answer here. Thank u.</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-4615><article id=article-comment-4615><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Cathy</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>December 29, 2016 at 2:12 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Thanks for the recipe. Can I use urad dal flour in this recipe? If so, what would the specific directions be?</p></div></article><ul class=children><li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id=comment-10427><article id=article-comment-10427><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>foram</span></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Yes, you can use the urad dal flour in this recipe.</p></div></article> </li></ul> </li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-4462><article id=article-comment-4462><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Gajanan Bant</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>November 5, 2016 at 11:03 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Knowing the cooking habits I found the recipe given is very nice and I will try to do as per the given ingredients&#8230;</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:100% class="rating-stars average rt_cls5"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id=comment-4212><article id=article-comment-4212><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Narayan Ponsamy</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>September 10, 2016 at 2:42 am</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Vrery good recipe, I will try to make it.</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:80% class="rating-stars average rt_cls4"></span></div></p></div></article> </li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id=comment-3419><article id=article-comment-3419><header class=comment-header><p class=comment-author> <span class=comment-author-name>Rojalee Panda</span></p><p class=comment-meta><time class=comment-time>April 1, 2016 at 5:48 pm</time></p></header><div class=comment-content><p>Thank you very much for amazing help with pics and tips. Now, I am going to make it in the breakfast&#8230;..</p><p><div class=base> <span style=width:80% class="rating-stars average rt_cls4"></span></div></p></div></article> </li></ol></div></main><aside class="sidebar sidebar-primary widget-area" role=complementary aria-label="Primary Sidebar" id=genesis-sidebar-primary><h2 class="genesis-sidebar-title screen-reader-text">Primary Sidebar</h2><section id=text-8 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><div class=textwidget><div id=sub_box><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Like Our Recipes? Follow Us!</h3><div id=soc_btn><div class="sub-icons clearfix" id=sprite_sub_icons> <a class=y-icon rel=external title="Follow foodviva on Youtube" href=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCFJWAH58LwIEDVMbBq-eCdw/ target=_blank></a> <a class=i-icon rel=external title="Follow foodviva on Instagram" href=https://www.instagram.com/foodviva/ target=_blank></a> <a class=facebook-icon title="Follow foodviva on Facebook" rel=external href=https://www.facebook.com/foodviva target=_blank></a> <a class=pinterest-icon title="Follow foodviva on Pinterest" rel=external href=https://in.pinterest.com/foodviva/ target=_blank></a> <a class=twitter-icon rel=external title="Follow foodviva on Twitter" href=https://www.twitter.com/foodviva target=_blank></a></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id=text-12 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><div class=textwidget><div class=side_img_widget><script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-4971890762803731" crossorigin=anonymous></script><br> <!-- Foodviva-336x280-SideBar-BelowFold-TextImage --><br> <ins class=adsbygoogle style="display: block;" data-ad-client=ca-pub-4971890762803731 data-ad-slot=5830536533 data-ad-format=auto data-full-width-responsive=true></ins><br> <script>(adsbygoogle=window.adsbygoogle||[]).push({});</script></div></div></div></section><section id=text-17 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Miscellaneous</h3><div class=textwidget><ul> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/diwali-recipes/ >Diwali</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/instant-pot-recipes/ >Instant Pot</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/baking-recipes/ >Baking</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/cooking-basics/ >Cooking Basics</a></li></ul></div></div></section><section id=text-16 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Regional Cuisine</h3><div class=textwidget><ul> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/north-indian-recipes/ >North Indian</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/south-indian-recipes/ >South Indian</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/gujarati-recipes/ >Gujarati</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/punjabi-recipes/ >Punjabi</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/rajasthani-recipes/ >Rajathani</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/maharashtrian-recipes/ >Maharashtrian</a></li></ul></div></div></section><section id=fv_popular-2 class="widget widget_fv_popular"><div class=widget-wrap><div class=widget_text><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Popular</h3><div id=tabs-popular><ul> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/snacks-recipes/white-sauce-pasta/ rel=bookmark title>White Sauce Pasta</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/dessert-recipes/eggless-vanilla-sponge-cake/ rel=bookmark title>Eggless Vanilla Sponge Cake</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/snacks-recipes/pav-bhaji/ rel=bookmark title>Pav Bhaji</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/snacks-recipes/pani-puri/ rel=bookmark title>Pani Puri</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/curry-recipes/paneer-butter-masala-recipe/ rel=bookmark title>Paneer Butter Masala</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/snacks-recipes/khaman-dhokla-recipe/ rel=bookmark title>Khaman Dhokla (Instant)</a> </li></ul></div></div></div></section><section id=recent-posts-2 class="widget widget_recent_entries"><div class=widget-wrap><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Recent Recipes</h3><ul> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/lunch-recipes/mung-beans-instant-pot/ >Mung Beans Instant Pot</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/desserts-sweets-recipes/stuffed-dates/ >Stuffed Dates</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/diwali-recipes/peda-ricotta-cheese/ >Peda with Ricotta Cheese</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/curry-recipes/mixed-vegetable-curry/ >Mixed Vegetable Curry</a> </li> <li> <a href=https://foodviva.com/mojito-recipes/blueberry-mojito/ >Blueberry Mojito</a> </li></ul></div></section><section id=text-13 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Cooking Tips</h3><div class=textwidget><div style="padding: 5px;">If your curry or dal turns salty, just add diced half-raw potato in it and boil for 5 minutes. Potato will absorb the extra salt.<br> <a href=https://foodviva.com/cooking-tips/ class=in_link>More Tips&#8230;</a></div></div></div></section><section id=text-18 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Beverages</h3><div class=textwidget><ul> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/mojito-recipes/ >Mojitos</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/smoothie-recipes/ >Smoothies</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/juice-recipes/ >Fresh Fruit Juices</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/milkshake-recipes/ >Milkshakes</a></li></ul></div></div></section><section id=text-14 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Popular Categories</h3><div class=textwidget><ul> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/paneer-recipes/ >Paneer Curries</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/kheer-halwa-recipes/ >Kheer and Halwa</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/snacks-recipes/ >Snacks and Starters</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/bhindi-recipes/ >Bhindi Curries</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/idli-dosa-recipes/ >Idli and Dosa</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/upma-recipes/ >Upma Recipes</a></li> <li><a href=https://foodviva.com/manchurian-recipes/ >Manchurian Recipes</a></li></ul></div></div></section><section id=text-7 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><div class=textwidget><div id=parent_gen_gallery style="margin-left: -20px;"><div id=general_gallery_display><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Food Gallery</h3><div><a title="Mohanthal- Click to View More Photos in Gallery" href=https://foodviva.com/gallery/page/12/ ><img class=slazy alt="Photo Gallery" width=125 height=125 data-original=https://cdn1.foodviva.com/static-content/food-images/desserts-sweets-recipes/mohanthal/mohanthal-250.jpg data-pin-no-hover=true></a></div><div><a title="Coconut Laddu- Click to View More Photos in Gallery" href=https://foodviva.com/gallery/page/13/ ><img class=slazy alt="Photo Gallery" width=125 height=125 data-original=https://cdn2.foodviva.com/static-content/food-images/desserts-sweets-recipes/coconut-ladoo/coconut-ladoo-250.jpg data-pin-no-hover=true></a></div><div><a title="Methi Puri - Click to View More Photos in Gallery" href=https://foodviva.com/diwali-recipes/page/3/ ><img class=slazy alt="Photo Gallery" width=125 height=125 data-original=https://cdn1.foodviva.com/static-content/food-images/snacks-recipes/methi-puri-recipe/methi-puri-recipe-250.jpg data-pin-no-hover=true></a></div><div><a title="Methi Puri- Click to View More Photos in Gallery" href=https://foodviva.com/desserts-sweets-recipes/gujiya/ ><img class=slazy alt="Photo Gallery" width=125 height=125 data-original=https://cdn1.foodviva.com/static-content/food-images/desserts-sweets-recipes/gujiya/gujiya-250.jpg data-pin-no-hover=true></a></div><div style="clear: both; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px;" align=center><a id=sgg_text_id href=https://foodviva.com/gallery/ >View More Photos in Gallery&#8230;.</a></div></div></div></div></div></section></aside></div></div><div class=footer-widgets id=genesis-footer-widgets><h2 class="genesis-sidebar-title screen-reader-text">Footer</h2><div class=wrap><div class="widget-area footer-widgets-1 footer-widget-area"><section id=text-3 class="widget widget_text"><div class=widget-wrap><div class=textwidget><div id=ft_link><a id=ft-2 title="Privacy Policy" href=https://foodviva.com/privacy-policy/ >Privacy Policy</a><a id=ft-3 title="Copyright Info" href=https://foodviva.com/copyright-info/ >Copyright Info</a><a id=ft-4 title="Terms and Conditions" href=https://foodviva.com/terms-and-conditions/ >Terms &amp; Conditions</a><a id=ft-5 title="About Us" href=https://foodviva.com/about-us/ >About Us</a><a id=ft-6 title="Contact Us" href=https://foodviva.com/contact-us/ >Contact Us</a><a id=ft-7 title="All Recipes List" href=https://foodviva.com/all-recipes-list/ >All Recipes</a><a id=ft-8 title="Latest Recipes List" href=https://foodviva.com/latest-recipes-list/ >Latest Recipes</a><a id=ft-9 title="Photo Gallery" href=https://foodviva.com/gallery/ >Photo Gallery</a><a id=ft-10 title=Cocktails href=https://cocktails.foodviva.com>Cocktails</a><a id=ft-11 title="foodviva.com in Hindi" href=https://hindi.foodviva.com>हिन्दी वेबसाइट</a></div></div></div></section></div></div></div><footer class=site-footer><div class=wrap><p>Copyright &copy; 2026 <a href=https://foodviva.com/ >foodviva.com</a> All rights reserved.<br></p></div></footer></div><script type=speculationrules>{"prefetch":[{"source":"document","where":{"and":[{"href_matches":"\/*"},{"not":{"href_matches":["\/wp-*.php","\/wp-admin\/*","\/static-content\/food-images\/*","\/wp-content\/*","\/wp-content\/plugins\/*","\/wp-content\/themes\/foodie-pro\/*","\/wp-content\/themes\/genesis\/*","\/*\\?(.+)"]}},{"not":{"selector_matches":"a[rel~=\"nofollow\"]"}},{"not":{"selector_matches":".no-prefetch, .no-prefetch a"}}]},"eagerness":"conservative"}]}</script> <script>document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded",function(event){var as=document.createElement("script");as.type="text/javascript",as.async=!0,as.src="https://cdn2.foodviva.com/wp-content/themes/foodie-pro/lazy_load.js.gzip";document.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(as);});</script><script>function wpcr_strpos(haystack,needle,offset){var i=(haystack+"").indexOf(needle,(offset||0));return i===-1?false:i;}
